The paper proposes a novel method for improving the results of GANs, which are commonly used in computer vision applications such as image generation and super-resolution. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training a discriminator, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The proposed method involves using feedback modules to improve the generator results, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the experiments involve image generation, which could also fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
